Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add
the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}, adding the beans for
the last ~{5%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to
the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and
discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the garlic and @Indonesian style spice mix{1%sachet} into the beef, then
cook for ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%g} in a sieve.

Add the sweetcorn, cooked green beans and rice to the beef. Mix well to combine.

Stir the @ketjap manis{50%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @sambal paste{15%g},
@honey{15%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce into the rice.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Share the beef fried rice between your #bowls{}. Enjoy!